===Etymology===
The name Hebei means "north of the (Yellow) River".

===Alternative forms===
* Chinese: {{zh-zh-p|河北|Héběi}}
* Wade-Giles: Ho-pei
* Postal map spelling: Hopeh
* One-character abbreviation is "冀" (pinyin: jì), named after Ji Province (冀州 Jì Zhōu), a Han Dynasty province (zhou) that included southern Hebei
* A common alternate name for Hebei is Yānzhào (燕赵), after the state of Yan and state of Zhao that existed there during the Warring States Period of early Chinese history.

